  "_note": "NB304: a light verb + a nominalization hides the action in a noun ('came to an agreement' -> 'agreed'). light_verbs are matched by lemma against the governing verb; nouns maps the nominalization lemma to the verb that replaces the whole construction. Matching is dependency-based (object of a light verb, or 'to'/'at' prepositional object of come/arrive), so articles, adjectives, and inflection don't matter.",
